title: Distribute Know Your Rights info to Amtrak and Greyhound passengers
description:
On April 13, 2025, US Border Patrol (USBP) agents boarded an Amtrak train at the Havre, MT station and systematically went up and down the train asking each passenger for their papers. Agents also questioned passengers who were on the platform stretching their legs during the train stop. 
  (https://www.havredailynews.com/story/2025/04/17/local/ice-questions-amtrak-passengers-in-havre-about-citizenship/547792.html) 

While no arrests were made that day by USBP or ICE officers during the incident, this was clearly an attempt to intimidate train passengers. We suppose that the purpose also was to establish a protocol for use by ICE or BP officers in other locations. 

Interstate transit passengers, regardless of their immigration or citizenship status, are entitled to the same Constitutional rights of liberty and due process, and against self-incrimination, unreasonable search and seizure.

In this action, we will distribute Transit Passenger Know Your Rights information to people at the Reno Amtrak station, which also serves as the Reno stop for Greyhound buses. The materials will be in English and Spanish; we are working on translations in Chinese and Tagalog.

We will start by distributing the booklet to westbound passengers, because the "100 mile zone" in which Customs and Border Protection has jurisdiction includes almost all of the train/bus route between Reno and San Francisco.. Choose among Friday times or Saturday times. 

"Know Your Rights"  fliers will be distributed either:
1)  in front of the train station, for actual trains, or
2)  at the bus stop across the street. Look for the Bus Stop sign. This is the boarding location for Amtrak buses and Greyhound/Flix buses. 

Join us in informing people of their Constitutional rights!

title: Texas Rising - Know Your Rights Info Session
description:
In the face of the hate speech dominating many national
conversations around immigration, it is crucial that
people know that the US Constitution provides certain
rights for everyone, regardless of immigration status.

There are steps that immigrants can take
to decrease their chances of detection, to protect
themselves in the event of contact with Immigration
and Customs Enforcement (ICE), and to prepare in the
event that a loved one is placed in removal proceedings. 

This virtual training will inform immigrant, their friends and family, and advocates on how to protect themselves affirmatively and defensively when in the presence of ICE. We are open to anyone interested in knowing and/or sharing how to protect your rights at home or in your neighborhood.

Zoom invites will be sent to attendees who have signed up prior to the event. Please sign up with an email address you have access to. This training will be available only in English but information on trainings in other languages can be found by reaching out to cameron@tfn.org

We should be able to make our voices heard at the polls and have a say in the leaders who represent us. But sometimes, politicians push for laws that discourage, obstruct, or even intimidate voters in an effort to cling to their power.

Polling place closures, limits to vote-by-mail, and needlessly strict voter ID regulations can prevent eligible voters from casting their ballot‚Äîand lately, this playbook of voter suppression strategies has become more popular. Common Cause is stopping voter suppression by opposing these efforts in the legislature, in the courts, and beyond in defense of the right to vote.

title: WORKSHOP | Yes, you can host a house party!
description:
**Why host a house party?**  Yes, door knocks, phone banks, postcards, rallies are all important organizing tools.  But in 2025-26, we need to do something more and different to win.  House parties can:

- Reach voters outside of our political bubbles

- Have friend and neighbor conversations with those who support our democratic values

- Inoculate voters against the onslaught of right-wing media

- Expand our volunteer base

 - How to plan your house party

 - Tips and tools for hosting conversations with your friends, neighbors, colleagues

*You'll leave the workshop fired up and ready to host your house party!*

Sign up here for ** *California* ** house party workshops - https://www.mobilize.us/cadems/event/759747/

For more Bay Area Coalition actions: https://bayareacoalition.org/
